Hi Charles,

MapSPAM gives you the irrigated area per crop, per pixel. To use Penman Monteith you will also need the crop calendar (from AQUASTAT: http://www.fao.org/nr/water/aquastat/water_use_agr/index2.stm), and meteorological data for the duration of the crop season (for each crop) - Wouter will know which is the best product for this (possibly Bastian's climatology). 

To start, I would calculate the reference evapotranspiration in each 5 arcminute grid cell using Penman-Monteith.

Then, for each crop type I would use Kc to get crop evapotranspiration. Then irrigation requirement (m3/m2) is the cumulative crop evapotranspiration (i.e. sum each day) during the growing season minus the cumulative rainfall during the growing season. To get a volume, multiply the m3/m2 value by the irrigated area from MapSPAM. 



